9 [ health insurance - fair coverage for individuals
with epilepsy - termination of coverage - coverage
10 for devices or surgeries for epilepsy - codification
- effective date ]
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6060.31 of Title 36, unless
16 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. All individual and group health insurance policies that
18 provide medical and surgical benefits shall provide the same
19 coverage and benefits to any individual who has been diagnosed with
20 epilepsy as the policy would provide coverage and benefits to an
21 individual who has not been diagnosed with epilepsy.
22 B. No insurer shall terminate coverage or refuse to renew an
23 individual's health insurance coverage solely based upon the
24 individual's diagnosis of epilepsy.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4294 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 C. To reduce the risk of death from sudden unexpected death in
2 epilepsy (SUDEP), all individual and group health insurance policies
3 that provide medical and surgical benefits shall adopt medical
4 policies that provide coverage for medically necessary
5 neurostimulation devices if prescribed by a licensed physician who
6 is actively treating the enrollee.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
8 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
April 20, 2026 - DO PASS AS AMENDED
